import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('Airport_Name').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by='counts', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Airport_Name'], data['counts'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Airport Name')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?')
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    aircraft_make_model = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().head(10)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(aircraft_make_model.index, aircraft_make_model.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Aircraft Make and Model')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    ax.set_title('What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Time_of_day'] = data['Time_of_day'].str.capitalize()
    time_of_day_counts = data['Time_of_day'].value_counts()
    time_of_day_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Time of Day')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by time of day?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

chart = plot(data)
